docs.abstract: From individual Twitter posts to orchestrated efforts by advocacy groups, the protests against the gun lobby have coalesced into a powerful movement.
docs.snippet: From individual Twitter posts to orchestrated efforts by advocacy groups, the protests against the gun lobby have coalesced into a powerful movement.
docs.lead_paragraph: Judith Pearson’s home in rural Minnesota is stocked with guns for hunting and recreational use, but that didn’t stop her from venting her frustration with the National Rifle Association after the deadly school shooting in Parkland, Fla.

headline.main: Big and Small, N.R.A. Boycott Efforts Come Together in Gun Debate
headline.print_headline: Protests Are Common. The Boycott of the N.R.A. Is Different.

docs.abstract: In two days on Capitol Hill, the Facebook chief promised numerous lawmakers that he would get back to them with answers to their questions. We counted up that workload.
docs.snippet: In two days on Capitol Hill, the Facebook chief promised numerous lawmakers that he would get back to them with answers to their questions. We counted up that workload.
docs.lead_paragraph: Facebook’s chief executive, Mark Zuckerberg — or perhaps more accurately, members of his staff —  are going to be very busy getting through a stack of homework.

headline.main: Mark Zuckerberg Has a Lot of Homework to Do
headline.print_headline: A Pile of Homework for Zuckerberg After His Visit to Congress

byline.original: By Sheera Frenkel and Tiffany Hsu

docs.abstract: The carrier will require more preflight documentation as a surge in animals used to aid disabled travelers and offer emotional support has raised safety concerns.
docs.snippet: The carrier will require more preflight documentation as a surge in animals used to aid disabled travelers and offer emotional support has raised safety concerns.
docs.lead_paragraph: Delta Air Lines said on Friday that it was tightening its rules for transporting service and support animals in an effort to reduce misbehavior by dogs and other creatures that air carriers are required by law to allow on board.

headline.main: Delta Air Lines Tightens Rules for Service and Support Animals
headline.print_headline: Delta Tightens Rules for Service and Support Pets

docs.abstract: The Trump administration is pushing a rule, first proposed under President Obama, to transfer and streamline oversight of commercial firearms exports.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration is pushing a rule, first proposed under President Obama, to transfer and streamline oversight of commercial firearms exports.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Trump administration wants to streamline the process for exporting American firearms, a change sought for years by domestic gun companies as a way to increase sales.

headline.main: A Bid to Increase Gun Exports, Stalled After Sandy Hook, Moves Ahead
headline.print_headline: Gun Exports Could Rise If New Rule Is Approved

byline.original: By Tiffany Hsu and John Ismay

docs.abstract: The president of Tennessee Technological University wrote to the E.P.A. saying the accuracy of the emissions study had been called into question.
docs.snippet: The president of Tennessee Technological University wrote to the E.P.A. saying the accuracy of the emissions study had been called into question.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The president of a Tennessee state university, under fire for an academic study on truck emissions that was paid for by a local trucking company, has asked federal officials to disregard the study, at least for now, in its review of pollution regulations that could benefit the company.

headline.main: University Pulls Back on Pollution Study That Supported Its Benefactor
headline.print_headline: University Pulls Back on Pollution Study That Supported Benefactor

docs.abstract: The post office has a bright spot in an otherwise dismal balance sheet: growth in its package delivery business, reflecting the boom in e-commerce.
docs.snippet: The post office has a bright spot in an otherwise dismal balance sheet: growth in its package delivery business, reflecting the boom in e-commerce.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Postal Service has many financial woes, but the health of its package delivery service is not one of them.

headline.main: Trump Targets a Postal Service Rainmaker: Package Delivery
headline.print_headline: Trump Targets a Postal Service Rainmaker

docs.abstract: At least three employees alleged inappropriate behavior by Wendell Jamieson, the metro editor, according to two people familiar with an internal investigation.
docs.snippet: At least three employees alleged inappropriate behavior by Wendell Jamieson, the metro editor, according to two people familiar with an internal investigation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Wendell Jamieson, the metro editor whose resignation was announced by The New York Times on Monday after an internal investigation, was accused of inappropriate behavior by at least three female employees, according to two people familiar with the investigation.

headline.main: Women Said to Accuse Times Editor Who Resigned of Inappropriate Behavior
headline.print_headline: Women Said to Accuse Times Editor of Inappropriate Conduct Before He Resigned

docs.abstract: Trevor Edwards will step down as brand president. He was seen as a potential successor to the chief executive, Mark Parker, who informed workers about reports of misbehavior at Nike.
docs.snippet: Trevor Edwards will step down as brand president. He was seen as a potential successor to the chief executive, Mark Parker, who informed workers about reports of misbehavior at Nike.
docs.lead_paragraph: Trevor Edwards, a top Nike executive who was seen as a potential successor to the chief executive, is stepping down, the company said on Thursday.

headline.main: Nike Executive Resigns; C.E.O. Addresses Workplace Behavior Complaints
headline.print_headline: A Top Nike Executive Steps Down, and the Chief Addresses Workplace Behavior

docs.abstract: A conservative backlash highlighted the challenge confronting corporations that are struggling to cater to both ends of America’s political and cultural poles.
docs.snippet: A conservative backlash highlighted the challenge confronting corporations that are struggling to cater to both ends of America’s political and cultural poles.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Delta Air Lines, one of Georgia’s largest private-sector employers, is among the glossiest corporate jewels in the state, contributing billions of dollars a year to the economy. Its hundreds of daily flights in and out of Atlanta’s airport are the main reason Georgia’s capital can brag, with justification, that it is a truly international city.

headline.main: In N.R.A. Fight, Delta Finds There Is No Neutral Ground
headline.print_headline: N.R.A. Battle Pits Business Against G.O.P.

byline.original: By Richard Fausset and Tiffany Hsu

docs.abstract: Before the age of buying with a click, generations knew there was a place where they could let their wishes whir.
docs.snippet: Before the age of buying with a click, generations knew there was a place where they could let their wishes whir.
docs.lead_paragraph: At Toys “R” Us, emotions always seemed to run high.

headline.main: Toys ‘R’ Us Customers Lament Store Closings: ‘I Want to Cry Right Now’
